# Hero Background Animation
I have implemented the requested 140-frame animation for the Hero section background.

## Changes Implemented

### 1. Animated Background in [HeroSection](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/components/HeroSection.tsx#10-222)
- Added a canvas-based frame player to [HeroSection.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/components/HeroSection.tsx).
- It preloads and cycles through [ezgif-frame-001.png](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/ezgif-frame-001.png) to [ezgif-frame-140.png](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/ezgif-frame-140.png) at 24fps.
- Ensures the frames cover the entire section (`object-cover` behavior).
- Removed the optional overlay to keep the visuals clean, but added a very subtle backdrop blur for text readability if needed. (Code has `backdrop-blur-[2px]`).

### 2. Assets
- Moved all 140 frame images to `public/hero-frames/`.

### 3. Cleanup
- Removed the global video background ([ex.mp4](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/assets/ex.mp4)) from [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/App.tsx) to improve performance and prevent visual conflict.
- Fixed a CSS syntax error in [src/index.css](file:///c:/Users/Janus/extro/janus-systems/src/index.css) where `@import` was incorrectly placed.

## Verification Results

### Automated Build
- `npm run build` passed successfully.
- Implies no TypeScript errors and correct asset references (for bundled assets).
- Frame images are in `public/` so they are served directly.

### Performance Note
- **Load Time**: The user is loading ~140 frames. This is heavy (approx 140MB).
- **Optimization**: The current implementation preloads images. Users might see a blank or static background until images load.
- **Future Improvement**: Convert frames to a WEBM/MP4 video for significantly better performance.
